'''Patricia Wynne''' is a freelance artist and illustrator with a career of over forty-five years. Specializing in scientific illustration, she has illustrated numerous scientific papers in collaboration with various scientists. She has also illustrated a number of children's books,<ref name="Medium">{{WebCite|url=https://medium.com/doverpublications/patricia-wynne-a-life-in-art-febb3df46ea2|text=Patricia Wynne: A Life in Art|work=[[Wikipedia:Medium (website)|Medium]]|author=[[Wikipedia:Dover Publications|Dover Publications]]|date=2017-05-23|archiveurl=https://archive.md/zmy0v}}</ref> including seven ''[[Star Wars]]'' storybooks published between [[1978]] and [[1980]].

The children's book ''Hello, Bumblebee Bat'', which Wynne illustrated, was a [[Wikipedia:Geisel Award|Theodor Seuss Geisel Award]] Honor book.<ref name="Charlesbridge">{{WebCite|url=https://www.charlesbridge.com/pages/patricia-j-wynne|text=Patricia Wynne|work=Charlesbridge|archivedate=20250912034626}}</ref> As the artist-in-residence at the Department of Mammalogy of the [[Wikipedia:American Museum of Natural History|American Museum of Natural History]] for over forty years, Wynne was honored as the namesake of a new species of bat in [[2014]]&mdash;''Thyroptera wynneae'', or "[[Wikipedia:Patricia's disk-winged bat|Patricia's disk-winged bat]]."<ref name="Bat" />

